Package executor.service.service.proxy

Interface ProxySourcesClient

All Known Implementing Classes:
HttpProxySourcesClient
public interface ProxySourcesClient
Interface for a client responsible for retrieving proxy configuration information.

The ProxySourcesClient interface defines a contract for classes that are responsible for retrieving proxy configuration information based on a provided username. Implementing classes should provide an implementation for the getProxy(String) method to retrieve and return a ProxyConfigHolder based on the specified username.

It is expected that implementations of this interface handle the communication with external sources, such as proxy servers or services, to dynamically obtain proxy configurations for scenarios.

Implementations may vary in terms of the source they use to obtain proxy information (e.g., HTTP, local configuration).

It is recommended for scenarios to use this interface to obtain the necessary proxy configurations based on specific requirements and configurations for different users or scenarios.

  • Method Details

    • getProxy

      ProxyConfigHolder getProxy(String username)
      Retrieves a ProxyConfigHolder for the specified username.

      The getProxy method is responsible for obtaining proxy configuration information based on the provided username. Implementing classes should define the logic to fetch and return a ProxyConfigHolder specific to the given username.

      The method takes a single parameter:

      • username: The username for which proxy configuration information is to be retrieved.

      The returned ProxyConfigHolder contains details about the proxy configuration, such as proxy host, port, credentials, etc. If an error occurs during the retrieval process, the method may return null or throw an exception, as specified by the implementation.

      It is expected that implementing classes handle communication with external sources, such as proxy servers or services, to dynamically obtain proxy configurations for scenarios.

      Implementers are encouraged to document any specific details or constraints related to the retrieval of proxy configurations based on the provided username.

      Parameters:
      username - The username for which proxy configuration information is to be retrieved.
      Returns:
      A ProxyConfigHolder containing the proxy configuration information for the specified username, or null if an error occurs during retrieval.
